defs.docs: Basic struct for `RGB` and `RGBA` pixels. Packed, with red first, alpha last.

defs.name: ComponentSlice
defs.docs: Casting the struct to slices of its components

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs: The components interpreted as an array, e.g. one `RGB` expands to 3 elements.

defs.name: ComponentBytes
defs.docs: Casting a slice of `RGB/A` values to a slice of `u8`

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: The components interpreted as raw bytes, in machine's native endian. In `RGB` bytes of the red component are first.

defs.name: as_bytes_mut
defs.docs: The components interpreted as raw bytes, in machine's native endian. In `RGB` bytes of the red component are first.

defs.name: map
defs.docs: Convenience function (equivalent of `self.iter().map().collect()`) for applying the same formula to every component.

defs.name: AsPixels
defs.docs: Casts a slice of bytes into a slice of pixels, e.g. `[u8]` to `[RGB8]`.

defs.name: as_pixels
defs.docs:
Reinterpret the slice as a read-only/shared slice of pixels.
 Multiple consecutive elements in the slice are intepreted as a single pixel
 (depending on format, e.g. 3 for RGB, 4 for RGBA).

defs.name: as_pixels_mut
defs.docs:
Reinterpret the slice as a mutable/exclusive slice of pixels.
 Multiple consecutive elements in the slice are intepreted as a single pixel
 (depending on format, e.g. 3 for RGB, 4 for RGBA).

defs.name: FromSlice
defs.docs: Cast a slice of component values (bytes) as a slice of RGB/RGBA pixels

defs.name: as_rgb_mut
defs.docs: Reinterpert mutable slice as RGB pixels

defs.name: as_rgba_mut
defs.docs: Reinterpert mutable slice as RGBA pixels

defs.name: as_bgr
defs.docs: Reinterpert slice as reverse-order BGR pixels

defs.name: as_bgra
defs.docs: Reinterpert slice as reverse-order BGRA pixels

defs.name: as_bgr_mut
defs.docs: Reinterpert ntable slice as reverse-order BGR pixels

defs.name: as_bgra_mut
defs.docs: Reinterpert mutable slice as reverse-order BGRA pixels

defs.name: Gray
defs.docs: Grayscale. Use `.0` or `*` (deref) to access the value.

defs.name: GrayAlpha
defs.docs: Grayscale with alpha. Use `.0`/`.1` to access.

defs.name: gray
defs.docs: Copy `Gray` component out of the `GrayAlpha` struct

defs.name: gray_mut
defs.docs: Provide a mutable view of only `Gray` component (leaving out alpha).

defs.name: map_gray
defs.value: fn <F, U, B> (&self, f: F) -> GrayAlpha<U, B>
defs.docs: Create new `GrayAlpha` with the same alpha value, but different `Gray` value

defs.name: RGBA8
defs.docs: 8-bit RGBA, alpha is last. 0 = transparent, 255 = opaque.

defs.name: RGBA16
defs.docs: 16-bit RGB in machine's native endian. 0 = transparent, 65535 = opaque.
